				<tr>
					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">On Final Fantasy 3, while I'm not sure but based on other FF games, it actually does maintain hidden save slots you cannot see. While there are 3 slots you can see it actually has others in memory which it falls back on if CRC checks fail. 
<br />
<br />If your theory is correct about NES and accessing SRAM while powering off causes it, then in theory using SRAM only for game state backup and only accessing it at very minimal times should eliminate the problem. But I seem to recall Zelda executes alot of code from SRAM. So maybe it is more likely to effect games which actively write to SRAM. Zelda probably doesn't write to it during gameplay.</div>

